Config:
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "sales-connector": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/absolute/path/to/server.js"]
    },
    "analytics-connector": {
      "command": "uv",
      "args": ["run", "/Users/you/projects/analytics/server.py"]
    }
  }
}

1) Test it in the Inspector with: uv run mcp dev /Users/you/projects/analytics/server.py — this opens a local UI to list and call the server's tools by hand.

2) With a relative path ("server.py"), the host would try to launch the server from its own working directory, not your project folder, so it would fail to find the file and the server would never connect. Absolute paths avoid this entirely.
